# Delete repo session

`C-d` should be available for a repo-backed named workspace entry even when
there is no live tmux session to close. Confirming should forget the workspace
and delete the workspace checkout.

    :bins jj tmux cat sh test

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'tmux', 'cat', 'sh', and 'test' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init beta (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R beta -m "beta commit" (exit: 0)
    :$ jj workspace add -R beta --name feature beta.feature (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R beta.feature -m "feature commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh -r 'beta*'; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 12 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

Filter to the repo-only named workspace entry. The header should offer deletion
even though the selected row has no live tmux sigil.

    :k feature C-n
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: feature
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-d] delete
   feature                                                                                                             ┃
▌  beta/feature                             ~/beta.feature                                                             ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  feature commit
│ ○  beta commit
├─╯
◆



```

Pressing `C-d` should mark the repo entry for deletion.

    :k C-d
    :settle (settled)
    :snap --color "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: feature
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-y] confirm
   feature                                                                                                             ┃
▌× beta/feature                             ~/beta.feature                                                             ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  feature commit
│ ○  beta commit
├─╯
◆



```

![light](delete-repo-session.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](delete-repo-session.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

Confirming should leave the picker alive, forget the workspace, and remove the
workspace checkout.

    :k C-y
    :settle -d 2s (settled)
    :snap

```terminal
session: feature
  0/3 | [C-r] repo: none
▌  feature                                                                                                             ┃
                                                                                                                       ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────







```

    :$ sh -c 'test ! -e beta.feature' (exit: 0)
    :$ jj workspace list -R beta --ignore-working-copy --no-pager --color never --template 'name ++ "\n"' (exit: 0)

```stdout
default
